<br>
I was sorry to see you go and said as much at the time, but your return does concern me.<br>
<br>
The reason I am so concerned is because since your departure from Blood Cult you haven't, from the evidence I have seen, changed.<br>
<br>
There is no reason to believe from the evidence before us that your not as combustable as an aerosol can in the raging fires of SolB as you where before.<br>
<br>
Rather than seeing an example of a change in your persona, instead your plea above shows a frightening example of the very thing you where guild removed for and I rather fear you are just applying for BC'ism on a rebound.  I hope that isn't the case.<br>
<br>
I try to be as direct as my convoluted ways allow me to be Jaynay, so i'll tell you strait now how I feel as I did when I consoled you on your departure, I very much feel that there is no need to rock the boat, I don't see any reason why BC should welcome you back.<br>
<br>
Nogi however believes in you.  His strength and faith in you alone is the reason you are being given this chance.  I sincerely hope he isn't doing this because he feels guilty about removing you, I hope his reasons are as just as his words of support have been.  His faith in you alone is the reason why I stand by his decision to let you back in.<br>
<br>
I have always maintained that I hold nothing against you Jaynay and even quite like you, and just as I said I was unhappy about the events that led to your departure and regreted your guildremoval.  I'll stand by my words when I said i'll continue to group with you and rez you if need be.<br>
<br>
I will not however, stand by and look on if you upset anyone else, guilded or otherwise, whilst wearing a Blood Cult tag after your name.<br>
<br>
Pneumatic.<br>
